	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />Try looking for a "Joycard Sansui SSS" pad, manufactured by Hudson Soft. Not only do they resemble Famicom pads (in dark grey), they have adjustable turbo fire, a headphone jack (really!), a thicker profile, rounded corners, and wonderful precision. The only problem I've had with them is that the middle turbo fire setting seems to die prematurely.

		

		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>


