	</tr>
	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />It's actually fairly easy to do a famicom to nes controller conversion.  When I found out my famicom was borked, I took off the player 1 controller, and hooked it up to the cord and plug from an old NES pad I had.  Now I play all my NES games with an awesome - 8+ foot corded famicom controller.  I mostly did it because i wanted a longer controller cord, but the famicom look is pretty cool too.
<br />
<br />Be careful though, and look at the connections on the circuit board inside of the case for BOTH controllers carefully before doing anything.  On mine, the wire colors did not match, even the the pinout did.   I'd show you guys a picture, but I'm not at home righ tnow.

		

		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>


